---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Ghana Scenario Analysis: Multiple Futures, Honest Probabilities"
  description="Scenario-based analysis of Ghana's economy. Multiple possible futures with probability estimates, indicator watchlists, and audience-specific implications."
  keywords="Ghana economic scenarios, Ghana economy forecast 2026, Ghana policy scenarios, Ghana investment risk scenarios"
>
  <div class="hero" style="padding-top:7rem;">
    <div class="hero-noise"></div>
    <div style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;position:relative;">
      <span class="hero-tag">Multiple Futures</span>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,2.8rem);font-weight:800;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:0.75rem;letter-spacing:-1px;">Scenario <span class="gradient-text">Analysis</span></h1>
      <p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;">Preparing for multiple futures is smarter than betting on one forecast. Each scenario analysis models 3 to 5 possible paths with honest probability estimates.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <h2>Coming Soon</h2>
      <p>Scenario analyses are advancing through the v3.0 publishing pipeline. The first scenario article (Ghana's Triple Shock: Hormuz, Cocoa, and GSE) is in development.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card coming-soon reveal">
        <span class="card-tag scenario">Scenario Analysis</span>
        <h3>Ghana's Triple Shock: Three Scenarios for 2026</h3>
        <p>Hormuz oil crisis, cocoa financing collapse, and GSE correction hit simultaneously. Base case (40-50%), upside (15-25%), downside (30-40%), and wildcard scenarios with indicator watchlists.</p>
        <div class="card-meta">
          <span class="pipeline-badge">Stage 1</span>
          <span>Target: April 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
